<DOC><DOCNO> AP880513-0048 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-13-88 0313EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-Japan-Markets 2ndLd-Writethru   05-13 0223</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Japan-Markets, 2nd Ld - Writethru,f0263,0224</SECOND><HEAD>Dollar Up, Stocks Post Big Gain</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with closing figures</NOTE><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The dollar finished the week higher Friday indealings against the Japanese yen, while stock prices posted astrong gain.   The dollar closed at 124.70 yen, up 0.31 yen from Thursday'sfinish. It had opened the day higher at 124.60 yen, and movedbetween 124.55 and 124.73 yen.   Traders said the dollar was moving higher in anticipation of aslight decline in Japan's trade surplus.   ``Market participants are also paying attention to U.S. tradefigures for March,'' said a dealer with a major commercial bank,who spoke on condition of anonymity. The U.S. figures are to bereleased next Tuesday in Washington.   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225selected issues, which won 51.53 points Thursday, gained another255.73 points, or 0.93 percent, to end the week's session at27,468.31.   A brokerage official, who also reguested anonymity, said shareprices rose almost across the board in early trading, as the marketcontinued on its bullish trend extending over from Thursday.   The official said a good overnight showing on Wall Street, inthe wake of recent declines, and good results from the refundingauction of U.S. Treasury bonds in the United States made investorsconfident about market prospects.</TEXT></DOC>